"a.简洁的 【英】 adj. 简洁的(brief or terse in speech or expression; concise) 【考】 audacious : trepidation / laconic : volubility(大胆的不会惊恐/简 洁的不会多话)laconic : speech / austere : design(简洁的演讲/朴素的 设计)反义词：garrulous( 多嘴的); verbose(冗长的); loquacious(多话的); voluble(多话的); 【记】 来自古希腊王国Lacon ia(拉哥尼亚)，以说 话简洁而闻名 adj. 说话简洁的 【记】来自古希腊王国拉哥尼亚, 以说话简洁而闻名 【类】audacious: trepidation = laconic: volubility大胆的不会惊恐 = 简洁的不会多话laconic: speech = austere: design 简洁的演讲简朴的设计dexterous: inept = voluble: laconic灵巧的不是笨拙的 = 多话的不是简短的 【反】garrulous(adj 多嘴的)verbose(adj 冗长的); loquacious(adj 多话的); voluble(adj 爱说话的) 【记】lack + nice 缺少，但是是好的缺少；简洁就是字少，但是是好的方面的少 laconic (adj.)  ""concise, abrupt,"" 1580s, probably via Latin Laconicus, from Greek Lakonikos, from Lakon ""person from Lakonia,"" the district around Sparta in southern Greece in ancient times, whose inhabitants were famously proud of their brevity of speech. When Philip of Macedon threatened them with, ""If I enter Laconia, I will raze Sparta to the ground,"" the Spartans' reply was, ""If."" An earlier form was laconical (1570s). Related: Laconically."
